  "body": " - Allow a local pool for any locally submitted changes\n - select from local pool first, then if that's empty we can select from gossiped messages\n\nstretch here would be\n - persist the local queue across restart\n - allow adding to the local pool any messages coming from api, even if they're already in the gossip queue\n - potentially re-gossip periodically anything still in the local queue, this could be randomly timed and should batch send, not flood.\n - local queue should accept messages before capella\n - local queue at capella fork should start batch gossiping with small breaks (eg. 125 / batch, wait 1s, next batch) ",
